text.tspan: Do winter and summer births have the same probability of being male?
There is no evidence in these data that the probabilities of a male birth
in summer and winter are different.
Seventy seven children were born in a hospital between 1-11 January 1986 (winter).
Between 1-11 July in the same year (summer), sixty four children were born in this
hospital. The genders of the children are shown in the table below.
